  "text": "The TLS configuration in Prometheus flows from high-level YAML configs through prometheus-common's HTTP configuration utilities to the final tls.Config object used in HTTP clients.\n\n## Configuration Definition Layer\n\nIn **prometheus/prometheus/config/config.go**:\n- **ScrapeConfig** (line 747): Defines scrape configurations with an embedded **HTTPClientConfig** field (line 830) that enables TLS configuration for scrape targets\n- **RemoteWriteConfig** (line 1419): Defines remote write configurations with an embedded **HTTPClientConfig** field (line 1434) for remote storage write endpoints\n- **RemoteReadConfig**: Similar structure with **HTTPClientConfig** for remote read endpoints\n- **AlertmanagerConfig** (line 1300): Defines alertmanager configurations with **HTTPClientConfig** field (line 1305)\n- **SetDirectory** methods: Recursively set file paths relative to config file directory, calling HTTPClientConfig.SetDirectory\n\n## HTTP and TLS Configuration Library\n\nIn **github.com/prometheus/common/config/http_config.go**:\n\n### Core Types:\n- **HTTPClientConfig** (line 75): Contains TLSConfig field (line 85) along with BasicAuth, BearerToken, and ProxyURL for HTTP client configuration\n- **TLSConfig** (line 328): Defines TLS parameters including CAFile, CertFile, KeyFile, ServerName, and InsecureSkipVerify flags\n- **BasicAuth** (line 40): Contains username and password for basic authentication\n\n### Key Functions:\n- **NewTLSConfig** (line 293): Converts prometheus-common's TLSConfig struct to Go's crypto/tls.Config. Handles:\n  - InsecureSkipVerify setting\n  - CAFile loading and root CA pool configuration\n  - ServerName validation\n  - Client certificate validation and loading via tls.LoadX509KeyPair\n  - File existence and permission checks\n\n- **NewClientFromConfig** (line 125): Creates an http.Client from HTTPClientConfig by:\n  - Calling NewRoundTripperFromConfig to build the transport\n  - Wrapping with bearer auth, basic auth round trippers\n  - Returning configured http.Client\n\n- **NewRoundTripperFromConfig** (line 135): Creates http.RoundTripper with:\n  - Calls NewTLSConfig to create tls.Config from TLSConfig\n  - Sets up http.Transport with TLSClientConfig field containing the tls.Config\n  - Configures proxy, keep-alives, timeouts, and connection tracking\n  - For CAFile with dynamic reloading, wraps with tlsRoundTripper\n\n- **newTLSRoundTripper** (line 388): Implements CA file hot-reloading by:\n  - Creating tlsRoundTripper wrapper that checks CAFile MD5 hash on each request\n  - Recreates tls.Config and RoundTripper if CAFile changes\n\n### Helper Functions:\n- **readCAFile** (line 357): Reads and returns PEM-encoded CA certificate file\n- **updateRootCA** (line 366): Parses PEM certificates and updates tls.Config.RootCAs\n- **getClientCertificate** (TLSConfig method, line 348): Loads client certificates via tls.LoadX509KeyPair\n\n## HTTP Client Creation in Scrapers\n\nIn **prometheus/prometheus/scrape/scrape.go**:\n- **newScrapeClient** (line 2260): Calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig (importing from prometheus-common) with HTTPClientConfig from ScrapeConfig, wraps transport with OpenTelemetry instrumentation, returns configured http.Client used for scraping metrics\n\n## Remote Storage Client Creation\n\nIn **prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/client.go**:\n- **ClientConfig** (line 128): Contains HTTPClientConfig field (line 131) passed to client creation functions\n- **NewReadClient** (line 151): Creates remote read client by calling config_util.NewClientFromConfig with HTTPClientConfig\n- **NewWriteClient** (line 183): Creates remote write client by calling config_util.NewClientFromConfig with HTTPClientConfig\n\nIn **prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/write.go**:\n- **Manager** (line 1): Manages remote write queues, constructs ClientConfig with HTTPClientConfig from RemoteWriteConfig\n- Creates NewWriteClient instances for each remote write endpoint using the HTTPClientConfig\n\n## Validation Layer\n\nIn **prometheus/prometheus/cmd/promtool/main.go**:\n- **checkTLSConfig** (line 790): Validates TLSConfig by ensuring:\n  - CertFile and KeyFile are both specified or both absent\n  - Files exist and are readable (unless checking syntax only)\n  - Returns errors for mismatched certificate/key pairs\n\n## Configuration Flow Summary\n\n1. User defines scrape_config or remote_write with tls_config YAML\n2. Prometheus YAML parser unmarshals into ScrapeConfig or RemoteWriteConfig structures containing HTTPClientConfig\n3. HTTPClientConfig contains TLSConfig with file paths\n4. SetDirectory methods resolve relative file paths\n5. During client creation, NewClientFromConfig is called with HTTPClientConfig\n6. NewRoundTripperFromConfig calls NewTLSConfig to convert TLSConfig to crypto/tls.Config\n7. NewTLSConfig:\n   - Reads CAFile and populates RootCAs\n   - Loads client certificates via tls.LoadX509KeyPair\n   - Sets ServerName for hostname verification\n   - Sets InsecureSkipVerify flag\n8. tls.Config is embedded in http.Transport.TLSClientConfig\n9. Optional tlsRoundTripper wrapper enables CA file hot-reloading\n10. http.Client uses this transport for all HTTPS connections to targets\n\nThe design allows dynamic reloading of CA certificates without restarting Prometheus, and propagates TLS configuration consistently across all HTTP connections (scraping, remote write, remote read, service discovery, alertmanager)."
}

